        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 28 at 6:36PM EST by NWS Pittsburgh PA</headline>
        <description>Scattered snow showers may continue through tonight before
tapering off towards midnight. While additional snowfall
accumulations are expected to be light, enough melting of the
snow on area roadways combined with falling temperature may
result in icy spots.

Untreated bridges and ramps are often the first surfaces to ice
up. Anyone traveling tonight should be alert for a wide range of
conditions and slow down in adverse weather conditions.
</description>
